# Git Rules

1. NEVER automatically commit or push changes without explicit user request
2. After making file changes:
   - Show what changes were made
   - Wait for explicit command to commit/push
   - Allow user to review changes if requested

3. Valid commit/push triggers are:
   - "commit these changes"
   - "push to git"
   - "push this"
   - Any explicit mention of git commit/push action

4. User can review changes first with:
   - "show me the changes"
   - "git status"
   - Any request to see current changes

5. Default behavior:
   - Make necessary file edits
   - Show changes
   - Wait for explicit git commands 